At this point I’ve seen a lot in surfing too many historic moments to count really, but there are a few that changed how I think about surfing and what is possible. 

One of those moments was around 2009 or 10 back when we thought jaws was a “tow wave”. It was valentines and very crowded with lots of questionable surfers because anyone can get whipped into a big wave. I was thinking how this needs to change and as I thought that I saw this stalky brazzilian paddling a 10 foot board in the channel with no vest on. Pretty sure the papaya board? Haha then he went over to the left in the middle of all the jet ski mayhem and paddled a couple absolute bombs. Changed everything I thought was possible in surfing in an instant. 

A year or two later when the first couple full paddle sessions started I didn’t have a board and @sos_shapes told me to hit up Marcio while he was shaping me one. He had to work the day of a mid size swell that was coming but gave me his 10ft board without a second thought and gave me some advice on lining up out there I still remember to this day. Got my first real paddle wave and my world changed again. 

He was a true legend. Someone who was able to glimpse beyond conventional wisdom at the next step and help us all get there. 

Wish I could tell you again how grateful I am for your help an inspiration you MAD DOG! Promise to keep that spirit alive ever session out there.

🎥 @takeshelterprod @jonspenser 
🎶 @zachlanebryan

Saw it’s brain health awareness month or something so here’s an update on mine. 

A lot of people have told me how stoked they are to see me back to normal since the concussion in 2019. I really appreciate that but the truth is I’m not and never will be whatever I considered normal before. 

It’s been over 3 years. I’ve been through lots of treatment’s, tried prescribed meds, meditating, therapy, fucken spirit quests you name it. I’m still a bit different. I can be shorter to anger (directed at myself), shorter to negative assumptions (very anxious) and even worse than I was at social interaction, which lead to a lot of self medicating that made things much worse. 

I’ve fucked up relationships and am generally a bit harder to be around. A lot of these traits I already had but they have been exaggerated since that wipeout. 

I did good at jaws this last run not cause “I’m back” but both because I was confident with my preparation, but also cause I had that “fuck it, nothing to lose” attitude. Which isn’t sustainable. So I’m still finding a balance there. 

Any way I have come a very long way since the worst of it and spend most days happy and still driven. I appreciate the people close to me more than I ever have. I’m now trying to move forward with a much more sober and clear headed approach and it feels like my best decision yet. 

I talk to a lot of people with head injuries on here so for anybody on similar journey, the point is don’t let the lows consume you and be okay with changes. Just keep putting in effort. Nothings permanent. 

🎶 @iprevailband

Since my concussion in 2019/20 winter we had two pretty average years where I was still in a daze a bit. Think only 4 waves made it from those seasons. 

Last year I was in a different kind of fucked up headspace. An angry one. It’s a little scary how well that can work. 

It’s always interesting to think of the why to do dangerous things. For me I think figuring out the edge of human potential is important and in brief moments we test it out there. But on the selfish side I want to leave a legacy out at this wave that can’t be fucked with. I think I’m half way there. If El Niño happens next year and I’m still in this head space, I’m a do some shit that ain’t been done.

Been trying my best to help during this tragedy but being good at surfing is a pretty fucken useless skill at the moment. I do have a reach because of it and that can help right now so I’ll do my best to update u all on what can help during this long process. 

@fresh_fish_maui and this crew have been getting good stuff done here and will continue to. Whatever funds they get will go directly to getting supplies out to people who need them or when the needs change it’ll go direct to families that need help now.

Check @mattmeola bio or my story for his Venmo. 

Another shout out to all my amazing friends and brother who fought the fires and all the other first responders.
And Thank you all, for the love your sending to this island.

Never been more proud to come from a family of first responders. Dad was a paramedic mom was an ER nurse and my brother (here) is a fireman. 

Just want to thank each and every single one of you.

When our island was hit with one of its worst disasters, from Lahaina all the way up to kula, you were all there for us and continue to be every day. 

You are all my heroes and proud to call a lot of u friends. 

Thanks @m1maui for the photo ❤️

Wild couple weeks. From needing a break of the island to never feeling more attached to it. 

Learned on my trip that I’m better at making new friends than I thought and remembered how many amazing people I know in this world. Also I conquered some serious social anxiety by going to @nfrealmusic concert sober and solo. 

Coming back home to this tragedy I was reminded how much respect I have for my friends and that this island is full of good people. I was also reminded how little social media reflects reality, saw much more love in person than online. 

Feels like a dumb self serving post in a time like this so here’s some useful information. @freshhelpmaui is in the process of becoming a legit non profit but in the mean time follow @fresh_fish_maui or @chimo_shippwreck for ways to contribute. 

We are setting a big silent auction event soon so be ready for that.

We are excited to be putting on a fundraiser night @paiabaycoffeeandbar this Saturday.

 There will be raffle, live music, silent auction and free @juneshineco for all first responders. Earlier in the night we have both a JJF and @torreymeister surf edit to show. Bring the kids! 

We will be opening the silent auction website soon with big ticket items like signed @john_john_florence @kai_lenny @rissmoore10  @ian.walsh boards, signed bike frame and kit by @camzink , As well as beautiful prints by @lahainalifestyle and a surfboard art piece by @annie__starr . There will be many local items to bid on as well. 

Thanks to partnering with  @changingtidesfoundation we will be operating under their 501c3 so all donations will be tax deductible and will go straight to the families of first responders that lost their homes. 

We hope this event can be one small step in the long journey to healing the island. Thank you everyone who’s been working hard on it.

@molokai2oahu was one of the harder things I’ve ever done but also one of the most rewarding. Came at a time when I think both @kai_paula and I needed a goal in the dead of summer both still a bit injured. 

I think I’m going to do this every year if I can, maybe even try solo next year. 

Thanks @mattmeola @mattsmithonmaui for coming with us was something I’ll never forget. Of course @barkboards for getting us this board and @lindsd3 and @kenzierobybrown for helping our recoveries. 

Just to keep updated the @freshhelpmaui silent auction site will be going up tomorrow morning sometime. Let any one u know who wants to help to get some high bids going on the signed boards and other gear.

Ima be honest… this didn’t end well. 

📷 @annie__starr

Had to give it a go yesterday. Couldn’t find anyone to come out (they were elsewhere scoring) but @annie__starr was there to watch over me. 

Went on the third wave of the set cause no sets had more than three waves till this one of course. Annie was right there ready for the pick up before the following wave but I waved her off to protect the ski and figured wave number 4 HAD to be the last wave of the set, in retrospect not my best call. 

After two more waves she was there again but we were so close to the cliff and I saw the next wave closing out into the worst area ever so I waved her off again (my bad again) then she was able to swing back in and get me. Right after we were back outside more waves came and idk how I woulda handled another set into the rocks. Ended up puking up some salt water for a while in the channel and some whiplash and other soreness but all in all pretty much fine. 

Very thankful all we lost was a board and a hat. Very thankful you were there @annie__starr you are a fucken insane ski driver.
